  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to FCC Community-Led Flood Migration</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &#x2018;Community-led Flood Mitigation Project&#x2019; project in Sierra Leone, implemented by Freetown City Council aims to establish community-led flood mitigation intervention to capacitate communities to identify and address their own flooding risks and mitigation strategies. The project objective is to reduce the risk of flooding which poses major sanitation and public health challenges including the spread of Cholera and other diseases in the city of Freetown.  Key project activities include setting up community-led teams, clearing critical flash flood points, in 3 communities, engaging the community and strengthening monitoring and enforcement of sanitation bylaws.</narrative>
  </description>
